        "en": "Historic Heart"
      },
      "title": {
        "en": "A Village Built on History"
      },
      "subtitle": {
        "en": "Greek refugees founded this dramatic clifftop settlement over 1,000 years ago."
      },
      "content": {
        "en": "Legend holds that 8th-century Greek refugees, fleeing religious persecution in the Byzantine Empire, discovered this hidden valley and established a settlement. The name 'Riomaggiore' derives from 'Rivus Major' (major stream), referencing the river that once flowed through the village center. The castle ruins above the village and the 14th-century Church of San Giovanni Battista testify to centuries of Mediterranean history."
      },
      "testimonial": {
        "quote": {
          "en": "Riomaggiore is the perfect base for exploring Cinque Terre. Great food, lively atmosphere, and you can hike to all the other villages. We stayed three nights and wished for more."
        },
        "author": {
          "en": "David Chen"
        },
        "role": {
          "en": "Hiking Enthusiast"
        },
