        "en": "Visitor Information"
      },
      "title": {
        "en": "Riomaggiore FAQs"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "Is Riomaggiore the best base for Cinque Terre?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "It's excellent for hikers and those wanting nightlife and restaurants. The train station provides easy access to all villages. For beaches, Monterosso is better."
          }
        },
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "Can I swim in Riomaggiore?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "Yes! The harbor has rock platforms for swimming and sunbathing. The water is crystal clear and deep. No sandy beach, but excellent for jumping in."
          }
        },
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "How do I access the hiking trails?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "Trails leave from the top of the village. The park office near the train station sells the Cinque Terre Card which includes trail access and train travel."
          }
        },
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "Is Via dell'Amore open?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "The famous 'Lovers Walk' to Manarola has been closed for repairs since 2012 but is partially reopening. Check current status with the park office."
          }
        },
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "What are the best restaurants?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "Dau Cila for seafood by the harbor, Rio Bistrot for modern Italian, Veciu Muin for traditional dishes, and A Pie de Campu for views and wine."
          }
        },
        {
          "question": {
            "en": "How far is La Spezia?"
          },
          "answer": {
            "en": "Just 8 minutes by train with departures every 15-20 minutes. La Spezia is the main transport hub for the region."
          }
        }
      ]
